comments.content:
I'm sure they're fonts -- I just don't have time right now to find them. But I'm posting the logo for the rest of the eager id-ers out there...   
   
 ![Wild Wing logo](http://web.archive.org/web/20071219181245im_/http:/www.typophile.com/forums/messages/83/36897.gif)
Though they might be fonts, I must say the "W"s aren't very consistent...
I think that has more to do with bad Illustrator/Corel customization to achieve the changes in height the designer desired. In doing so I think the designer simply messed up the angles.
It reminds me of the work of one of those $50 Logo websites.

It's very close to the [Marlboro typeface](http://web.archive.org/web/20071219181245/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/urw/marlboro/neo-contact-d/testdrive.html?s=WILD%2BWING&p=72), but let me see if I can get any closer. That middle serif on the W is kind of the killer.
They just lowered it so it would match the line between the words.
